<section class="section">

<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
Environmental microbiomics applies sequencing and computational biology to study microbial communities in natural and built environments. These microbial systems influence nutrient cycling, ecosystem stability, water quality, soil health, climate processes, pollution response, and environmental exposure.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, environmental science is presented as a core microbiomics research area: a bridge between microbial ecology, ecosystem monitoring, environmental health, infectious disease surveillance, antimicrobial resistance, and multi-omics environmental systems biology.
</p>

</section>

